# Environment Variables

## Required for Production

### OpenAI API
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-...
# Get from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# Used for: ASR transcription (Whisper) and AI scoring (GPT-4o-mini)

### Supabase (Public)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxxx.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGc...
# Get from: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API
# Used for: Client-side auth and anon-key queries

### Supabase (Server)
SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxxx.supabase.co
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJhbGc...
# Get from: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API
# Used for: Server-side database operations (bypasses RLS)

### Admin Access
ADMIN_EMAIL=your-admin@example.com
# The email address that has admin access to /admin routes
# Must match the email you use to log in

## Required Supabase Project Settings (Dashboard, not env vars)

### Allow anonymous sign-ins  ← REQUIRED for guest mode
# Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Sign In / Providers
#   → Anonymous Sign-Ins → toggle "Allow anonymous sign-ins" ON
# Without this, the homepage "继续为访客 · 无需注册" button errors out.
# Tightening recommendation for production:
#   Auth → Rate Limits → set anonymous sign-ins per hour (default 30/IP)

## Optional

### Development
NODE_ENV=development
# Automatically set by Next.js, no need to configure
